        <updateDate>2013-05-23T18:09:38Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Constitutional Amendment - Prohibits denial or abridgement of the rights of a crime victim to fairness, respect, and dignity. Grants a crime victim the right: (1) to reasonable notice of, and to not be excluded from, public proceedings relating to the offense; (2) to be heard at any release, plea, sentencing, or other such proceeding involving any right established under this amendment; (3) to proceedings free from unreasonable delay; (4) to reasonable notice of the release or escape of the accused; (5) to due consideration of the crime victim's safety and privacy; and (6) to restitution.</p> <p>Grants the crime victim, or the victim's lawful representative, standing to fully assert and enforce such rights in any court. </p> <p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
    <title>Proposing an amendment to the Constitution of the United States to protect the rights of crime victims.</title>
